Subject: ARM64 syscall compatibility - add __ARCH_WANT_NEW_STAT
Upstream: No
Origin: Fedora qt5-qtwebengine (aarch64 compatibility)
Author: Wolfi OS Maintainers

ARM64/aarch64 architecture uses newfstatat syscall instead of legacy stat syscalls.
The __ARCH_WANT_NEW_STAT definition ensures the kernel headers provide the correct
syscall numbers for ARM64 systems.

Without this patch, the seccomp sandbox may fail on ARM64 with missing syscall
definitions for fstatat operations.

--- a/src/3rdparty/chromium/sandbox/linux/system_headers/arm64_linux_syscalls.h
+++ b/src/3rdparty/chromium/sandbox/linux/system_headers/arm64_linux_syscalls.h
@@ -7,6 +7,8 @@
 #ifndef SANDBOX_LINUX_SYSTEM_HEADERS_ARM64_LINUX_SYSCALLS_H_
 #define SANDBOX_LINUX_SYSTEM_HEADERS_ARM64_LINUX_SYSCALLS_H_

+#define __ARCH_WANT_NEW_STAT
+
 #include <asm-generic/unistd.h>

 #if !defined(__NR_fstatat)
